A customs officer, ASC11 Mohammed Maradun, who was shot by bandits in Kaduna is dead. Suspected armed bandits had on Wednesday stormed his residence at Rigachikun, a community of Igabi Local Government Area of Kaduna, and shot while six persons were abducted. The customs officer who was attached to the Federal Operations Unit (FOU), Zone B, Kaduna, was immediately rushed to the hospital for treatment but died while undergoing surgery. Confirming his death on Thursday, FOU Chief Public Relations Officer (CPRO), M.A Magaji said his corpse will be conveyed to his home state of Zamfara for burial later today.